<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
The type specimen of this species was damaged seriously, lacking the abdomen, thorax, all legs, one elytron and part of head, but its aedeagus has been kept well, of which dorsal plates of parameres are separated (Figs 19−21), which is a diagnostic character of 
<taxonomicName authority="Gorham, 1889" authorityName="Gorham" authorityYear="1889" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Lycocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lycocerus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Lycocerus</taxonomicName>
(Okushima, 2005). This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Gorham, 1889" authorityName="Gorham" authorityYear="1889" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Lycocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lycocerus canthariformis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="canthariformis">Lycocerus canthariformis</taxonomicName>
(Ishida, 1986) (located in Japan) in the pronotum, which is rounded, wider than long, lateral margins are arcuate and posterior angles rounded, but the aedeagus is differs from that of the latter. Also, it is related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Gorham, 1889" authorityName="Gorham" authorityYear="1889" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Lycocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lycocerus pubicollis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pubicollis">Lycocerus pubicollis</taxonomicName>
(Heyden, 1889) in the aedeagus, but obviously different from the latter in the pronotum. Consequently, we suggest the following new combination: 
<taxonomicName authority="Gorham, 1889" authorityName="Gorham" authorityYear="1889" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Lycocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lycocerus swampingatus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="swampingatus">Lycocerus swampingatus</taxonomicName>
(Pic, 1916), comb. n.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
